data.database_description: This database is designed to manage and organize healthcare facility operations by tracking various entities involved in patient care. It includes tables for physicians, nurses, patients, departments, medications, procedures, appointments, hospital rooms, and on-call schedules, with relationships among these entities facilitating comprehensive management of medical services. The schema supports functionalities such as assigning primary physicians to patients, managing staff certifications and affiliations, scheduling appointments, tracking medication prescriptions, and recording patient stays in hospital rooms for specific treatments or procedures. Additionally, it enables efficient handling of room availability and nurse on-call assignments, ensuring coordinated care delivery within the healthcare facility.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each physician.
Full name of the physician
Professional position or title of the physician
Social Security Number of the physician for identification

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Details physicians working in the healthcare facility including their roles and identification.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for a department
Name of the department
Identifier for the head physician, linking to Physician.EmployeeID

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains information about hospital departments including their leaders.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for a physician, linking to Physician.EmployeeID
Identifier for a department, linking to Department.DepartmentID
Boolean indicating if the affiliation is primary

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks the affiliation of physicians to departments and indicates primary affiliations.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each procedure.
Descriptive name of the medical procedure.
Financial cost associated with performing the procedure.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about medical procedures including their codes, names, and associated costs.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier linking to a physician who is certified in the treatment.
Code of the procedure that the physician is trained in.
The date on which the physician's certification for the treatment was granted.
The expiration date of the physician's certification for the treatment.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks certifications for physicians regarding specific treatments, including certification dates and expiration.

columns.columnDescription: Social Security Number serving as a unique identifier for each patient.
Full name of the patient.
Residential address of the patient.
Contact phone number for the patient.
Identifier for the patient's insurance provider.
Primary Care Physician assigned to the patient, linked to Physician.EmployeeID.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about patients including personal details, insurance, and primary care physician.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each nurse.
Full name of the nurse.
Job title or role within the healthcare facility.
Boolean indicating if the nurse is registered with relevant authorities.
Social Security Number for identification purposes.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about nurses, including their roles and registration status.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each appointment.
Foreign key linking to the Patient table, identifying the patient attending the appointment.
Foreign key linking to the Nurse table, indicating the nurse preparing for the patient's appointment.
Foreign key linking to the Physician table, identifying the physician conducting the appointment.
The start time and date of the appointment.
The end time and date of the appointment.
Location where the appointment takes place, indicating the specific room used for examination.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Manages details of patient appointments including staff assignments and timings.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each medication.
Generic name of the medication.
Brand name under which the medication is marketed.
Additional details or description about the medication.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains details of medications available in the healthcare facility.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier linking to the physician who prescribes the medication.
Identifier linking to the patient receiving the prescription.
Identifier linking to the prescribed medication.
Timestamp of when the prescription was made.
Identifier linking to the appointment associated with this prescription.
Dosage information for the prescribed medication.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks prescriptions made by physicians for patients, including details of medications and appointments.

columns.columnDescription: Identifies the floor number of a block in the hospital.
Unique code assigned to each block for identification.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Represents physical blocks within a healthcare facility where rooms are located.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for a specific room.
Describes the type of room (e.g., Single, Double).
Associates the room with a floor in the hospital block.
Links the room to its corresponding block.
Indicates whether the room is currently unavailable for use.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains details about individual rooms within blocks, including their availability.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier linking to the Nurse table's EmployeeID.
The floor number where the nurse is on call.
A code representing a specific block or area for on-call duty.
Start time of the on-call period.
End time of the on-call period.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks nurses' on-call schedules, including their assigned locations and timeframes.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for a patient's stay record.
Links the stay to a specific patient using their SSN.
Identifies the room number where the patient stayed.
Records the start date and time of the patient's stay.
Records the end date and time of the patient's stay.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks patient stays in rooms, including start and end times.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier linking to a patient who is receiving the procedure.
Code of the procedure that the patient is undergoing.
Identifier for the hospital stay during which the procedure occurs.
The date on which the patient undergoes the procedure.
Identifier of the physician performing the procedure.
Identifier of the nurse assisting with the procedure.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records details about patients undergoing specific medical procedures, including dates and involved staff.
